<HEADLINE>
FT  10 DEC 94 / Weekend Money (Investing for Income): Gilt issues - best
value v tax status
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Gilt issues - best value v tax status
Your capital gain on a gilt - a UK government bond - is tax free.
However, you pay tax on the interest. Therefore, gilts which deliver a
higher proportion of their total return as capital gain are more tax
efficient, and - other things being equal - more attractive to
higher rate taxpayers.
 ---------------------------------------------------------------------
NON-TAXPAYERS
             Stock                      Price       Yield  Volatility
                                                        %            %
 ---------------------------------------------------------------------
CONVENTIONAL
       &lt;5yr  Conversion 10.25%, 1999    106 11/16   8.57%    3.85%
     5-10yr  Treasury    9.75%, 2002    105 27/32   8.68%    5.29%
    10-15yr  Treasury   11.75%, 2003/07 116 1/16    9.91%    5.21%
