<HEADLINE>
FT  10 DEC 94 / Weekend Money (Investing for Growth): Proteus
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Proteus International has had a miserable year, with its shares falling by
more than 70 per cent at one stage. It hopes to 'design' effective drugs
using computer software developed at Manchester University. But the company
has failed to inspire investors suspicious of the scientific credentials of
top management, which started out in the property business, and of the
quality of the software.
Its most successful research programme has been in animal drugs, an area
with lower safety standards and sales than human treatments.
</TEXT>
