<HEADLINE>
FT  10 DEC 94 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MAN PRODUCTEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Early this week pepper prices started stabilising at the lower levels
reached during the previous week, reports Man Producten. Accumulated selling
pressure, mainly from India and Brazil, and the lack of buying interest in
consuming markets sent prices down steeply. However, buyers gradually
realised the sudden drop might be overdone and from the middle of the week
values began slowly to recover. Black pepper, faq, ended at about US2,400 a
tonne and white at Dollars 3,450.
