<HEADLINE>
FT  10 DEC 94 / Weekend Money (Budget Fallout): Smokers, drinkers and
drivers hit by mini-Budget
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Thursday's mini-Budget, resulting from the government's defeat over
extending VAT on fuel to 17.5 per cent, was bad news for smokers, drinkers
and drivers. Duty on alcohol and tobacco is raised by about 4 per cent from
midnight, December 31. This means an extra 6p on 20 cigarettes, 1p on a pint
of beer, 5p on a bottle of wine, and
26p on a bottle of whisky. Duty on petrol and diesel will go up by 1p a
litre (4.5p a gallon) at the same time. Planned extra payments to compensate
pensioners and social security claimants for the higher VAT rate will be
scaled back. The earnings threshold for NI contributions will be Pounds 58
rather than Pounds 59 a week from April 1995.
